  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Education at Primary Schools</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the districts of Shabunda and Walungu, the program reaches out to a total of 40.000 children in 90 primary schools. A total of over 800 teachers and 40 government staff in the districts are directly involved in the program. At provincial level we contract the department of education and the inspection.At provincial level we contract the department of education and the inspection.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project boosts the enrollment of children in 90 Primary schools as well as the quality of education provided through improving quality of school management, involvement of parents&#x2019; associations, governance, and teaching. RBF strengthens the education system through improved collaboration and accountability between all actors. It aims to provide good quality education for all</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We aim to (i) improve access to education,especially for girls and vulnerable children (ii) improve quality education and (iii) strengthen the educational system: the management at the 90 schools and at the provincial level. 90 primary schools are contracted and receive subsidies based on indicators of improved access, quality, and parent satisfaction. The promotion of good, effective and efficient governance, transparency and accountability at all levels are key.</narrative>
  </description>
